I made songs from my parent’s basement in a country town with a population of 3000 people. After years of trying, people actually heard those songs. 
These past couple of years, I slowed down and took some time to really enjoy the process of creating with no pressure, grow as a man, and really reflect and be grateful for what God has done in my life. 

This is still the beginning of the journey, but I’ve learned to live in my blessings instead of always waiting for the next one. 

Thank you for sticking around. 
If you’re new, welcome. 
Journey continues soon.
2023 crazy. This message will self destruct💣

I believe that everyone’s life is a rare, unique, and beautiful art piece that only they can build and finish. The next record serves as a reminder to anyone that’s doubting the path they’re on to let them know that they’re right where they’re supposed to be and that their life is worth it. It’s something that we all need to hear at one point or another. When you realize this, it’s easier to be at peace with your journey. 

See you soon🎨

Life is a beautiful thing! Mine is a masterpiece🎨

- Bob Floss™️

I want to stress to creatives how important it is to give yourself a BREAK. Life happens, and sometimes it can throw several haymakers at once. In 2020, I found myself in that exact situation. I was blessed to be doing what I loved, but things in my personal life were really weighing me down and keeping me from fully appreciating what was happening or being as consistent as I needed to be.  Instead of beating yourself or forcing yourself, use that time to pray, get clarity, refocus, rebuild, get inspiration, and create something even better. Above anything else, your mental space matters and is the most important. You can’t be the best artist you can be if you’re not healthy. 

Love always.

I started playing the keys when I was 6. Something about there being endless combinations and possibilities to express myself through different sounds intrigued me. I have an understanding of keys and scales, but I can barely even read music. Everything comes from my mind and the colors I see when I hear the individual notes. 

Anyway, quick lil lick before the day gets started. Win the day, brotato chip🤞🏾

My Black Mom

In the beginning, it was me in by parent’s basement in a country town of 3,000 people trying to figure out how I was going to make this dream happen. 

No matter what was going on in my life or where I was, I could tune everything out and get lost in melodies. 

Eventually things started to happen! However, I eventually let the industry opinions, politics, and fake love blind me of why I really do this. To be honest, I simply love this, I can’t help but create, and it’s my purpose to share stories and an important perspective. 

At the end of the day, if nobody ever pressed play, the value of my music wouldn’t have been any less because it means so much to me. I hope that in whatever you do, you realize this too.

My muse, you illuminate my thoughts.

The cover of “VibeNineThree” was inspired by a picture of a young Quincy Jones in the studio. Growing up, I used to watch my favorite producers in the studio over and over every single day on YouTube when I got home from school. I always used to wonder “What was on their mind when they were creating?” 

Now that I’m in the same position I realize that most of us are thinking the same thing: “What can I do to bring the vision in my head to life?”

 That’s the beautiful thing about music. We’re all constantly just figuring it out. 

Same thing with life, I suppose.

The World Is Yours!

Time is the finest of luxuries, savor the moments.

Falling! ft. @sorenbryce this Friday, Sept 1st. 

When this whole thing started happening, I was on Cloud 9. I thought all of the love was genuine and that everyone that was around cared about me. However when I went through a rough time in 2020 and needed to take a break, many of those same people either betrayed me or gave up on me for one reason or another. It seemed like everything in my personal life was crumbling at the same time. 

Nevertheless, it made me a man and made my art 10x better. I learned from what I went through and my life completely changed. My art became even bigger than it was before, the woman of my dreams came into my life, and I took more time to appreciate the genuine people who love me. 

You all have no idea how much your positive words helped me during that time, even though you may not have known what I was going through. This song is for anyone who is doubting your worth, your journey, and your ability to work through the changes. I hope you always understand that better times are on the other side of the pain you’re going through right now. 

Can’t wait to share this one with you.

Black is Brilliant.

Saying that you’re the woman of my dreams would be inaccurate because I couldn’t have ever imagined that someone like you actually existed. 

You’ve brightened up my world and changed my life. You give me unprecedented peace in a world of chaos, materialism, and unrest. 

You make me a better man, a better  creator, and a better human being. I thank God every single day that your existence has been intertwined with mine.
Grateful to have air circulating through these lungs to experience this gift that we call life

This has been a goal in the back of my mind for a long time. Many challenges, roadblocks, losses, lessons, and sacrifices along the way. Thank you for listening, connecting, and supporting me while I’ve taken the time to grow as a man, lock in, and evolve into the creative I was always meant to be. Taking the time to detach from the industry, has been one of the best things I’ve done. 

I’ve really only shared 40% of what I’m actually capable of thus far, and I’m excited to share what I’ve been up to these past couple of years, this upcoming year. 

Big love and remember that the only limits you have are the ones you put on yourself.

Life Update: I married my best friend💍

My Wife, 

You came into my life at a time where I honestly didn’t know if I’d ever settle down. You’ve celebrated me as man, given me unprecedented peace, provided boundless inspiration, and encouraged me when things aren’t going as planned. 

On this couch, we’ve held each other. We’ve laughed, we’ve cried, and experienced each other in our truest forms. I’ve never met a woman like you in my existence in its entirety. 

You fine, you mine, and you’re one of a kind. Cheers my love🥂

📸: @ryan_harris_films

2023 has been the most important year of my life thus far. This year my biggest focus was self improvement, as I realized that to be the very best that I could be for others, I have to be the best me I possibly can. I gave my last name to the most phenomenal woman I’ve ever met in my existence. I reached goals that I’ve been working towards since the very beginning. I made the best music (and albums😉) of my life. I realized that working out is actually one of my favorite outlets outside of music. Most importantly, I realized that I am enough and always have been, even before any of this. 

If you have ever connected with me, my music, or something I’ve said, I’m extremely and genuinely grateful for you. With that being said, I owe you an album (or two). One more feature coming tomorrow and after that, we shall groove❤️
